panese for pushing the boundaries, and they've really come a long way over the past 2 decades to wear the crown in ""extreme"" film-making, but ""Devil's Experiment"" just does even more. Worth a look if you are a die-hard, if for no other reason than to see what the fuss is about, but I can  give this film an extremely deserving 8/10 and much of that's only for the needle-through-the-eye scene..."	1
